  <title>Map the tablet buttons</title>

  <comment>
    <cite date="2012-04-21" href="mailto:mdhillca@gmail.com">Michael Hill</cite>
    <p>If the graphics tablet has buttons, map functions to each one. List the
     possible functions in a table.</p>
  </comment>

  <p>Short introductory text...</p>

<steps>
  <item><p>Click the user menu on the right side of the taskbar and select
   <gui>Settings</gui>.</p></item>
  <item><p>Open <gui>Wacom Tablet</gui>.</p>
     <note style="tip"><p>If no tablet is detected, you'll be asked to
      <gui>Please plug in or turn on your Wacom tablet</gui>.</p></note>
  </item>
  <item><p>Next to <gui>Tracking Mode</gui>, select <gui>Tablet (absolute)</gui>
   or <gui>Touchpad (relative)</gui>.</p></item>
</steps>


